# Program-using-string-
coding:
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String str1 = "Hello";
        String str2 = "World";
        String str3 = "hello";
        String result = str1 + " " + str2; 
  System.out.println("Concatenated String: " + result);
        System.out.println("Length of str1: " + str1.length());
        System.out.println("Are str1 and str3 equal? " + str1.equals(str3)); 
        System.out.println("Are str1 and str3 equal (ignore case)? " + str1.equalsIgnoreCase(str3));
        System.out.println("str1 in uppercase: " + str1.toUpperCase());
        System.out.println("str2 in lowercase: " + str2.toLowerCase());
        System.out.println("Does str1 contain 'll'? " + str1.contains("ll"));
        String replacedString = str2.replace('o', 'a');
        System.out.println("Replaced 'o' with 'a' in str2: " + replacedString);
        String substring = result.substring(6, 11); // Extract "World"
        System.out.println("Substring of result: " + substring);
        String sentence = "Java is fun!";
        String[] words = sentence.split(" "); 
        System.out.println("Words in the sentence:");
        for (String word : words) {
            System.out.println(word);
        }
        String strWithSpaces = "   Java Programming   ";
        System.out.println("Before trim: '" + strWithSpaces + "'");
        System.out.println("After trim: '" + strWithSpaces.trim() + "'");
    }
}

output:Concatenated String: Hello World
Length of str1: 5
Are str1 and str3 equal? false
Are str1 and str3 equal (ignore case)? true
str1 in uppercase: HELLO
str2 in lowercase: world
Does str1 contain 'll'? true
Replaced 'o' with 'a' in str2: Warld
Substring of result: World
Words in the sentence:
Java
is
fun!
Before trim: '   Java Programming   '
After trim: 'Java Programming'
